  "title": "Real Estate Agent Finds the House Has Squatters — All Snakes",
  "script": "Snakes moved in — rent-free? A Century 21 agent named Christopher White drove to rural central Arkansas to show a listing. Vacant house, no utilities. He pulled up, walked to the door — and found a snake trying to get THROUGH it. Not the yard. The door. Another one was dangling off the outdoor electrical conduit. He pulled out his phone. Shot video. Inside the breaker box: snakes. On the porch: more snakes. Gary McKim from D&G Varmint Control came out and confirmed: all black rat snakes — non-venomous — moved in to mate and eat mice from the nearby fields. Christopher told his buyer there would be no tour that day. House is still listed. How much of a discount would YOU need on that asking price?",
